    <div class="luxury-block">
      <div class="lux-label">🧊 Standalone Ice Maker Repair</div>
      <h3>Why standalone units need brand-specific service</h3>
      <p>A Scotsman undercounter ice maker and a Samsung fridge ice maker share almost no parts and use completely different cooling and water delivery systems. Standalone units have their own refrigerant sealed system, their own drain pump, and their own water distribution boards. They also produce a different ice type, most standalone units make "gourmet" or "nugget" ice with specific crystal formation that requires precise water temperature and flow control.</p>
      <p>In SoCal's hard water environment, standalone units in entertaining kitchens that see heavy use need descaling every 6 months, more frequently than the standard 12-month recommendation. We've seen Scotsman and U-Line units with severe scale buildup after only 8 months of service in Beverly Hills, Newport Coast, and Pacific Palisades homes. The fix is straightforward when caught early; a complete system cleaning when caught late takes significantly more time.</p>

